Are We Being Bad Citizens If We Don't Keep Up With the News?

In your opinion, are we being bad citizens if we don't keep up with the news? Do you think all people have some responsibility to know what is going on in the world? Does engaging with current events actually do anything at all? Why do you think the way you do?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: we all have a responsibility to know how we can make a difference not only for ourselves and our immediate communities but on the grander scale as well.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I believe news of what is happening in the world helps broaden our perspective, get us to think of people outside of our lives, and

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The news, however, has become all about ratings, and they don't give us the most reliable information anymore.
